### Scenario
An internal web application provides a `/profile` endpoint that displays a user’s profile information (full name, email address, and mailing address). The endpoint accepts a `user_id` query parameter supplied by the client. Only the owner of the profile or users with an administrator role may view any profile. The application must retrieve the requested profile from a data store, render the data into a simple HTML page, and return it to the browser. When access is denied or the profile does not exist, a standard error page must be returned instead of the profile content.

### Functional Requirements
- Accept a `user_id` query parameter from the HTTP request.
